16/12/2004
TOKYO, Japan -- Japan's government said Wednesday (15 December) that it will remove the need for entry and short-stay visas for Bulgarian citizens starting in January 2005.
The announcement, which came on the third day of Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg's five-day visit to Japan, is part of a joint Partnership Declaration he signed with Japanese Prime Minister Junichiro Koizumi.
During his stay, Saxe-Coburg also called for an increase in Japanese investments in Bulgaria.
In other news, Bulgaria's President Georgi Parvanov is expected to visit NATO Headquarters and hold talks with Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer in Brussels Thursday.
Parvanov will also participate in the EU summit.
(Sega, Monitor, NATO Web site - 16/12/04)
